body:
Yes. This commit added this explicitly a long time ago: https://github.com/go-swagger/go-swagger/commit/0df6cf44896e6fcf88aa2d1f57da3afeb3981766. The nullable status is forced here https://github.com/go-swagger/go-swagger/blob/f032690aab0634d97e2861a708d8fd9365ba77d2/generator/types.go#L249

It remains unclear to me why we wanted this and above all why we wanted to override any `x-nullable` setting.
@casualjim do you perchance recall why we specifically wanted all `allOf` structs to be forced as nullable?
